<I>No Rest for the Wicked</I></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueloriar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EloriaR</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/22/01 8:33:19 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lower Level/Money Version of Same Request</span><hr size=1> Ok, been there myself with the same questions regarding wisdom and no money.  At lvl 29 you can start doing ports when you aren't busy and can pick up 10-30pp each time you spend a little time at it - it depends how you charge, whether you do any charity cases such as CR or the like. I often try one port out of Kunark for cash each day when I am done, then gate back to camp. Went from 150pp after buying lvl 29 spells to over 600pp at lvl 31 after purchases. <br>
<br>
Now for wisdom stuff, you didn't say what your base wisdom is, just that it is 102 now. Assuming this is close to your base wisdom, your first , relatively cheap purchases can be +2 wis rings approx 4-5 pp a pair<br>
+2 wis earings 7-10 pp (pair) if you know a jeweler, 30-40pp otherwise<br>
+4 wis silver ruby veil guessing around 100-200pp <br>
splitpaw gloves +2 wis dropped in SK and Split Paw by gnolls<br>
+3 wis blackened iron medalion dropped in Runnyeye<br>
+3 wis PBB dropped in beholders by named EE doable by 2-3 at lvl 29-30<br>
<br>
Sorry cant help you with prices of these dropped items, I had a BIM given to me when I was lvl 5 or 6 by a much older druid out of kindness and camped the rest, buying a second PBB for 150pp which was probably too much but I was 'rich' from doing ports. It also helps to have a jeweler in my guild.<br>
<br>
Don't forget the Testament quest for +10 wis either.<br>
<br>
--Eloria Rivermist<br>
lvl 31 Soldier of Tunare<br>
